prtcl is a visual exploration thought touch and tilt. Particles are created driven by x+y logic, enticing the user to search for predictability in their behaviour.

Features:
- Retina support
- Create particles by moving your fingers across the screen
- Manipulate their color values and their speed
- Use accelerometer instead of automated motion - tilt your device while simultaneously drawing new particles

Ver 1.0 Created at the V&A Decode Openframeworks Workshop in London 28/02/2010
Thanks To Zach Lieberman, Joel Gethin Lewis, Kyle Mcdonald, Arturo Castro, Andreas Muller, Eduard Prats Molner, Zach Gage, onedotzero and Victoria And Albert Museum.

Created with openFrameworks

